floatingpointdev.parameters
Class Parameter

java.lang.Object
  floatingpointdev.parameters.Parameter
All Implemented Interfaces:
floatingpointdev.toolkit.util.IObservable
public class Parameter
extends java.lang.Object
implements floatingpointdev.toolkit.util.IObservable

A Parameter Object is simply a variable that holds a floating point value that is bounded by a minimum and a maximum.

Author:
floatingpointdev

getValNormalized

public float getValNormalized()
Returns the value of this parameter normalized between 0 and 1.

Returns:
the value of this parameter normalized between 0 and 1. if valMin is 0 and valMax is 1, then getVal() and getValNormalized return the same thing.

setVal

public void setVal(float val)
Set the value of this Parameter.

Parameters:
val - the value to set this Parameter to. Note that the value is bounded by valMin and valMax. So if you attempt to set the value above valMax then the value will simply be set to valMax. Likewise for valMin.

setValNormalized

public void setValNormalized(float val)
Sets the value of this Parameter using the range (0-1). So if you want to set the Parameter to 75% you can call setValNormalized(.75).

Parameters:
val - the normalized value to set the parameter to. acceptable range: (0-1) If valMin is 0 and valMax is 1, then setVal() and setValNormalized function exactly the same.

setValMinAndMax

public void setValMinAndMax(float min,
                            float max)
Sets the minimum and maximum values that the Parameter's value can have. valMin must be less than valMax. If valMin is greater or equal to valMax then the function fails and does nothing.

Parameters:
min - the minimum value for this Parameter.
max - the maximum value for this Parameter.

setValMin

public void setValMin(float min)
Set the minimum value for this Parameter. Default valMin is 0.

Parameters:
min - the minimum value for this Parameter. Note that if you attempt to set valMin above valMax then valMin will not be changed.

setValMax

public void setValMax(float max)
Set the maximum value for this Parameter. Default valMax is 1.

Parameters:
max - the maximum value for this Parameter. Note that if you attempt to set valMax below valMin then valMax will not be changed.
